  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Does installing an EV charger increase my Brisbane home's sale price?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "A properly installed level 2 wall charger typically adds $3,000 to $6,000 to a Brisbane home's perceived value, which is usually more than the install cost of $1,500 to $3,500. The effect is strongest in Brisbane's inner east, where EV ownership is higher than the city average and buyers actively screen for charging infrastructure."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What types of EV charging do buyers look for in a Brisbane home?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Three tiers: level 1 (a standard 10-amp power point, adds around 10km of range per hour), level 2 (a dedicated wall-mounted charger on a 32-amp circuit, 40 to 60km of range per hour), and three-phase charging (the fastest home option, found in homes with three-phase power). Level 2 is the current expectation for most buyers; three-phase is a premium feature for higher-end EV owners."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can I advertise my Brisbane property as 'EV ready' if there is no charger installed?",
